<hr>
<div class='commentinfo comment_comment'>
2008-05-04 07:23:54 (2218 days ago)
<div id='contact-1'>x (1)</div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
As of May 2008, there's a new Riverside Park on this section of the Cape Fear in Erwin (at the Hwy<br/>
217 bridge): canoe/kayak access, walking trails, overlooks, restrooms, a shelter and space for<br/>
outdoor education. Two groups put in almost $1 million to tame the landscape there: non-profit<br/>
Harnett (Co.) Forward Together and the N.C. Parks and Recreation Trust Fund. It's managed by the<br/>
town of Erwin, NC, and Harnett Co. Parks/Rec. Getting up the steep riverbank there is almost<br/>
heavenly now. </div>
</td>
</tr>
